  "prompt": "How do I get IR with my Samsung Galaxy 7 so I can use my phone as a TV remote?",
  "response": "To use your Samsung Galaxy S7 as a TV remote, you can take advantage of the built-in IR (Infrared) blaster and the \"Peel Smart Remote\" app. Here's how you can set it up:\n\n### Step 1: Check for the IR Blaster\nConfirm that your Galaxy S7 has an IR blaster. This feature was available on the S7 and S7 Edge, so ensure your model supports it.\n\n### Step 2: Download the Peel Smart Remote App\nThe Peel Smart Remote app is pre-installed on many Samsung devices, but if it\u2019s not on your phone, you can download it from the Google Play Store.\n\n1. Open the **Google Play Store**.\n2. Search for **\"Peel Smart Remote\"** (or a compatible IR remote app).\n3. Install the app.\n\n### Step 3: Set Up the Peel Smart Remote App\n1. Open the **Peel Smart Remote** app.\n2. Follow the on-screen instructions to set up your TV or other IR-controlled devices.\n   - The app will ask you to select your TV brand and model.\n   - If your device is not listed, the app will try to auto-detect it.\n3. Once set up, you can use your phone as a remote for your TV, cable box, or other IR devices.\n\n### Step 4: Use the IR Remote\n1. Open the **Peel Smart Remote** app.\n2. Select the device you want to control (e.g., TV).\n3. Use the on-screen buttons to control your device, just like a physical remote.\n\n### Alternative Apps\nIf the Peel Smart Remote app doesn\u2019t work for you, there are other IR remote apps available on the Play Store, such as:\n- **Sure Universal Remote**\n- **IR Universal Remote**\n- **Smart Remote**\n\n### Notes\n- Ensure your phone\u2019s IR blaster is not blocked by a case or other obstruction.\n- The IR blaster on the Galaxy S7 is located near the top of the phone.\n\nEnjoy using your Samsung Galaxy S7 as a TV remote!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
